WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074


02:47.990 --> 02:49.690
Oh, this is great!

02:49.690 --> 02:50.690
Wow!

02:50.690 --> 02:51.790
Oh, that's incredible.

02:51.790 --> 02:54.390
There's got to be seven
or eight feet up there.

02:54.890 --> 02:57.390
And eighty years of dust.

02:57.890 --> 02:59.090
Look at all this height.

02:59.190 --> 03:00.390
We could put our
bedroom upstairs

03:00.390 --> 03:01.989
and that will leave us with
all this space.

03:01.989 --> 03:03.389
For what?

03:03.389 --> 03:05.589
Just space.

03:06.190 --> 03:07.790
One!

03:07.891 --> 03:09.491
Two!

03:09.491 --> 03:11.090
Three!

03:12.490 --> 03:14.690
- And four?
- Come on.

03:16.491 --> 03:18.291
And five?

03:20.190 --> 03:21.690
Watch, watch!

03:21.690 --> 03:23.990
God, this place is huge.

03:26.790 --> 03:27.990
It's beautiful.

03:27.990 --> 03:29.689
God!

03:29.789 --> 03:31.990
You guys, it's absolutely incredible.

03:32.190 --> 03:34.190
Incredible.

03:34.190 --> 03:35.790
A little paint.

03:36.090 --> 03:38.389
Sell it tomorrow,
double your money.

03:38.489 --> 03:40.790
Carl, you're obsessed.

03:40.890 --> 03:42.591
A little bit.

03:42.591 --> 03:44.791
Wow, look!

03:46.490 --> 03:48.490
Hey, it's an Indian head penny.

03:48.490 --> 03:50.890
1898.

03:52.890 --> 03:54.890
It's a good omen.

03:55.590 --> 03:57.990
You're the good omen.

04:01.589 --> 04:03.490
Oh, it's so great!

04:12.988 --> 04:16.288
I had Rose move your 3 o'clock
with Bob Kahan to 4 o'clock.

04:17.088 --> 04:18.889
Gary Alan called at the end
of the day yesterday.

04:18.889 --> 04:22.289
He has to see you about the
final painting bids for the loft.

04:22.389 --> 04:24.889
3 o'clock is the only time
he can make it. Is that OK?

04:25.789 --> 04:27.490
Sam?

04:30.190 --> 04:31.889
Ah? I'm sorry.

04:31.889 --> 04:34.689
Relax, man. This is
not brain surgery.

04:35.089 --> 04:37.989
Pitching these Japanese guys
makes me so nervous.

04:38.689 --> 04:40.188
Sam...

04:40.288 --> 04:42.388
You're going to be great. OK?

04:42.988 --> 04:44.789
What am I supposed to say?

04:44.789 --> 04:48.788
I can't really tell them my
Swedish girl joke, you know.

04:49.188 --> 04:50.488
Great. Where did
you get those?

04:50.488 --> 04:52.489
Nice, huh? Molly.

04:52.489 --> 04:54.890
What do you think?
Are they me?

04:55.090 --> 04:57.090
Oh, man. Look at
that, a Testarossa.

04:57.190 --> 04:58.089
Wow.

04:58.089 --> 05:00.789
- Ouch!
- Pay off your Mustang first.

05:11.489 --> 05:12.589
How are you?

05:12.589 --> 05:14.189
What did the doctor say?

05:14.189 --> 05:15.989
He said that it was contagious.

05:15.989 --> 05:16.989
That it was really...

05:17.089 --> 05:18.789
- No?
- Yeah.

05:18.789 --> 05:21.689
He said I shouldn't
even be coming in today.

05:22.489 --> 05:24.189
What about the rash?

05:25.488 --> 05:26.588
The rash?

05:26.888 --> 05:28.789
The rash is...

05:28.989 --> 05:30.289
also incredibly contagious.

05:30.289 --> 05:32.190
He said they've
both been spreading.

05:32.190 --> 05:33.989
No?

05:37.089 --> 05:39.290
On your genitals again?

05:39.390 --> 05:40.690
Yeah.

05:40.690 --> 05:42.689
Yeah, right on the genitals.

05:43.089 --> 05:44.589
Basically everywhere.

05:44.589 --> 05:46.489
He said that I
shouldn't touch anyone.

05:47.787 --> 05:49.687
Excuse me, I'm sorry.

05:53.286 --> 05:54.987
- You're sick.
- I know.

05:54.987 --> 05:56.387
Morning, Paul.

05:56.487 --> 05:58.687
- Carl, Sam.
- Save it, Paul.

06:00.086 --> 06:01.786
Morning, Susie.
You're looking good.

06:01.786 --> 06:03.087
Sam.

06:03.087 --> 06:05.088
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.

06:07.188 --> 06:09.287
- Here it is.
- Thanks.

06:11.587 --> 06:13.387
- Morning, Sam.
- Morning, Rose.

06:13.387 --> 06:14.487
Listen, the Kobiashi people...

06:14.487 --> 06:16.587
They're already here.

06:16.687 --> 06:18.687
- They're early!
- I know.

06:18.687 --> 06:21.287
- Come here.
- Andy Dillon called...

06:21.287 --> 06:23.486
- How long have they been here?
- About ten minutes.

06:23.486 --> 06:24.486
Andy Dillon called.

06:24.486 --> 06:28.086
And he says he needs $ 900,000
transferred to Albany by ten.

06:28.086 --> 06:30.086
- By ten?
- Yes.

06:32.786 --> 06:33.886
- Carl?

06:33.886 --> 06:35.386
Yeah?

06:38.085 --> 06:40.886
Dillon needs 900,000 in Albany by ten.

06:41.086 --> 06:42.587
Can you transfer it
to his account?

06:42.587 --> 06:44.287
Yeah, but I need your MAC code.

06:44.287 --> 06:46.186
OK.

06:52.287 --> 06:53.786
Discretion, right?

06:53.786 --> 06:54.886
Got it.

06:54.886 --> 06:56.286
You bet.
I'll do it right now.

06:56.386 --> 06:57.686
Thanks.

06:57.686 --> 06:59.586
Bill, I'll call
you back.

07:10.586 --> 07:12.185
OK, that's fine.

07:12.285 --> 07:13.986
That's fine.

07:15.286 --> 07:17.487
Oh, man, this
is too far out.

07:18.887 --> 07:20.886
Can you get this, man?

07:21.886 --> 07:22.886
Where you guys from

07:22.986 --> 07:24.886
the New York City Ballet?

07:29.186 --> 07:31.186
Almost.

07:34.986 --> 07:35.986
Saved your life!

07:35.986 --> 07:37.486
You shit!

07:37.486 --> 07:38.686
You scared me to death.

07:38.686 --> 07:39.786
Why did you do that?

07:39.786 --> 07:43.086
It's better than seeing this gorgeous
body splattered all over the place.

07:43.286 --> 07:45.186
Look out!

07:51.385 --> 07:52.086
Grab it!

07:52.086 --> 07:54.187
Sam, Moll!
Are you guys home?

07:54.187 --> 07:55.287
Carl! Did you invite him?

07:55.287 --> 07:56.386
Slave labour.

07:56.386 --> 07:57.886
- Carl!
- What?

07:57.886 --> 07:59.786
- Hurry, help!
- Oh, my God.

07:59.786 --> 08:01.286
Grab the bottom.

08:01.286 --> 08:03.087
Now, go there.

08:04.787 --> 08:05.786
Right here?

08:05.786 --> 08:07.686
Watch your toes.

08:08.586 --> 08:09.686
Where do you want this?

08:09.686 --> 08:11.886
In the bedroom.

08:13.586 --> 08:15.685
God, this place looks great!

08:16.185 --> 08:16.985
Yeah.

08:17.085 --> 08:18.086
You like it, huh?

08:18.086 --> 08:19.786
Like? Like is
hardly the word.

08:19.786 --> 08:22.386
I had no idea it would be
this beautiful. It's incredible.

08:22.486 --> 08:23.985
Molly, what about her?

08:23.985 --> 08:26.886
Why don't you just leave her
there until the other stuff is here.

08:26.886 --> 08:28.287
What are these?

08:28.287 --> 08:29.987
Oh, let me show you.

08:30.087 --> 08:31.886
Will you help
me lift this up?

08:34.686 --> 08:35.586
Wow.

08:35.586 --> 08:37.186
Just finished it.
What do you think?

08:37.186 --> 08:39.186
It's fantastic.
I love it.

08:40.486 --> 08:42.486
Sam, what's this
chair doing here?

08:43.785 --> 08:45.086
What do you mean?
I love that chair.

08:45.086 --> 08:47.485
I know you love this chair,
but we discussed this and...

08:47.485 --> 08:49.386
I've had it forever.

08:49.785 --> 08:51.785
When I watch TV, I sit in it.

08:51.885 --> 08:53.485
This chair is ugly.

08:53.685 --> 08:55.785
- So?
- And it doesn't go with anything.

08:55.885 --> 08:57.785
It goes with me.

08:58.285 --> 09:00.284
You're right, it does.

09:01.484 --> 09:03.085
We'll paint it.

09:03.085 --> 09:04.385
We'll what?

09:13.486 --> 09:15.486
Are you OK?

09:16.186 --> 09:18.285
I'm fine.

09:20.885 --> 09:22.985
What's the matter?

09:23.585 --> 09:25.684
Nothing.

09:28.784 --> 09:30.885
Are you worried
about the promotion?

09:33.085 --> 09:35.284
No, not really.

09:44.185 --> 09:45.585
Then what?

09:45.785 --> 09:47.885
Moving in together?

09:47.985 --> 09:49.685
No.

09:53.485 --> 09:54.885
I don't know.
It's...

09:54.885 --> 09:57.185
a lot of things.

10:00.786 --> 10:04.185
I just don't want
the bubble to burst.

10:05.885 --> 10:07.785
It seems like...

10:09.685 --> 10:12.284
whenever anything good
in my life happens

10:12.284 --> 10:14.785
I'm just afraid
I'm going to lose it.

10:20.085 --> 10:22.785
I love you.

10:22.985 --> 10:24.986
I really love you.

10:27.686 --> 10:29.485
Ditto.

10:31.985 --> 10:33.685
The pilot's first report
of trouble was

10:33.685 --> 10:35.185
the blew the number
two engine

10:35.185 --> 10:38.184
the one in the tail of the plane.
It was fully loaded...

10:39.484 --> 10:41.885
Oh, Jesus.
Another one?

10:43.785 --> 10:45.585
Don't watch that.

10:47.184 --> 10:48.885
I should cancel
my LA trip.

10:48.885 --> 10:51.286
These things always
happen in threes.

10:52.886 --> 10:54.985
Sam, get serious!

10:54.985 --> 10:57.485
Besides, you lead
a charmed life.

10:57.885 --> 10:59.585
Yeah, so did they.

11:01.285 --> 11:02.685
It's amazing.

11:02.685 --> 11:03.784
Just like that...

11:03.984 --> 11:05.885
Blackout.

12:13.182 --> 12:15.081
What are you doing?

12:15.982 --> 12:17.982
I couldn't sleep.

12:20.382 --> 12:21.682
Boy.

12:22.582 --> 12:24.582
I really must have
passed out.

12:24.882 --> 12:27.182
What time is it?

12:27.182 --> 12:29.382
It's 2 am.

12:52.582 --> 12:53.782
Oh, no.

12:53.882 --> 12:56.682
I hope it wasn't
a masterpiece.

12:56.682 --> 12:58.982
Well, it's not now.

13:00.781 --> 13:02.081
Can I help?

13:02.181 --> 13:03.081
Yeah.

13:03.081 --> 13:06.282
Put your hands here.
Now get them wet.

13:08.482 --> 13:12.082
Let the clay slide
between your fingers.

16:05.480 --> 16:07.279
Oh, no.

16:08.479 --> 16:10.379
What's the matter?

16:11.079 --> 16:12.980
A glitch.
What's up?

16:12.980 --> 16:16.480
The Greenberg and White accounts,
I can't get in. The macro doesn't work.

16:16.480 --> 16:17.580
I changed it.

16:17.580 --> 16:21.380
- Chaned it? Why?
- I just want to nose around a bit.

16:21.480 --> 16:23.581
Is something wrong?

16:24.981 --> 16:26.980
Can you keep a secret?

16:28.280 --> 16:30.080
Yeah, sure.

16:30.180 --> 16:31.580
What's up?

16:31.580 --> 16:33.480
There's too much money
in these accounts.

16:33.480 --> 16:36.179
Too much money?
That's impossible.

16:41.780 --> 16:44.679
Sam, this is going
to take you hours.

16:44.679 --> 16:47.380
- Let me do this.
- It already has taken me hours.

16:47.380 --> 16:49.481
Well, let me figure
it out for you.

16:49.681 --> 16:50.781
No, it's OK.

16:50.781 --> 16:52.880
It's like a vendetta now.

16:53.480 --> 16:54.580
Thanks, though,
I appreciate it.

16:54.580 --> 16:56.280
OK.

16:56.280 --> 16:58.380
If you start to go
blind, just give a shout.

16:58.480 --> 17:00.180
OK. AdiÃ³s.

17:01.279 --> 17:04.680
Listen, I was wandering what are
you and Moll doing tonight?

17:04.880 --> 17:07.680
We're going to the theatre.
She wants to see Macbeth.

17:07.980 --> 17:10.180
I think she likes the
guys in tights.

17:10.579 --> 17:12.780
- You want to go?
- No. Thanks.

17:12.780 --> 17:14.579
I want a full report, though.

17:14.780 --> 17:17.680
- Later.
- Yeah.

17:22.079 --> 17:23.880
Well, I loved it.

17:23.880 --> 17:25.981
I was spellbound
the whole time.

17:25.981 --> 17:28.180
I could tell, and so could
the rest of the audience

17:28.180 --> 17:30.780
with that resonating
snore of yours.

17:37.180 --> 17:39.380
Did I tell you what
Marcia said?

17:39.380 --> 17:40.880
Yeah, about six times.

17:40.980 --> 17:44.178
It wasn't six times.
Quit being so blase about this.

17:44.178 --> 17:45.477
OK. Sorry.

17:45.577 --> 17:46.577
This was really important.

17:46.577 --> 17:48.877
I'm going to have
two pieces in her gallery.

17:48.978 --> 17:52.878
The New York Times
reviews her gallery all the time.

17:52.978 --> 17:56.978
Molly, the New York Times is just some
frustrated critic with pimples on his ass

17:56.978 --> 17:58.378
who flunked art school.

17:58.378 --> 18:01.079
Who cares what they think?

18:01.079 --> 18:03.878
About 8 million readers,
that's who.

18:03.878 --> 18:07.778
No, they're just reading
the sports page.

18:07.878 --> 18:10.078
Your work is
really beautiful.

18:10.078 --> 18:12.078
It really is.

18:12.277 --> 18:14.478
And it shouldn't matter
what anyone else thinks

18:14.478 --> 18:16.578
just what I think.

18:21.377 --> 18:23.577
I want to marry you, Sam.

18:23.777 --> 18:25.577
What?

18:26.577 --> 18:27.677
What?

18:27.677 --> 18:29.677
Yeah.

18:29.677 --> 18:31.676
I've been thinking about it.

18:31.676 --> 18:34.176
I've been thinking
about it a lot.

18:34.577 --> 18:37.378
And I think we should just do it.

18:37.478 --> 18:39.377
Are you serious?

18:39.577 --> 18:41.277
Yeah.

18:44.578 --> 18:46.778
What's that look for?

18:50.677 --> 18:54.277
You never wanted
to talk about it.

19:03.577 --> 19:05.677
Do you love me, Sam?

19:06.276 --> 19:08.377
What do you think?

19:09.777 --> 19:11.378
Why don't you ever say it?

19:11.378 --> 19:14.678
What do you mean "why don't I ever say it"?
I say it all the time. I feel like...

19:14.678 --> 19:18.277
You say "ditto."
That's not the same.

19:20.677 --> 19:21.977
People say "I love you"
all the time

19:21.977 --> 19:24.277
and it doesn't
mean anything.

19:27.577 --> 19:31.677
You know, sometimes
you need to hear it.

19:32.677 --> 19:35.077
I need to hear it.

19:35.577 --> 19:37.477
Let's go.

19:45.976 --> 19:46.977
What should we do?

19:46.977 --> 19:48.378
Let me handle it.

19:48.478 --> 19:49.478
What do you want?

19:49.478 --> 19:51.877
Your wallet!
Give it!

19:51.977 --> 19:55.077
Sam, just give it to him.

19:56.378 --> 19:59.477
OK. Just take the money.
Just leave...

19:59.477 --> 20:01.577
No! Sam!

20:01.777 --> 20:03.777
You son of a bitch!

20:05.777 --> 20:07.777
Sam! No!

20:08.576 --> 20:10.276
Somebody help us!

20:10.476 --> 20:12.577
Jesus Christ, Sam!

20:14.177 --> 20:15.477
Just get off him!

20:15.477 --> 20:17.177
Somebody!

20:17.177 --> 20:19.076
Somebody help us!

20:19.176 --> 20:21.077
Sam...

20:22.478 --> 20:24.078
Just stop it!

20:24.078 --> 20:25.978
Stop it, Sam!

20:45.576 --> 20:47.576
Molly?

20:49.276 --> 20:51.176
Molly! You got...?

21:03.176 --> 21:05.676
Oh, baby, hold on.

21:05.776 --> 21:07.877
You're going to be OK.

21:09.777 --> 21:11.176
Somebody?

21:11.276 --> 21:12.876
Somebody!

21:12.876 --> 21:14.876
Somebody help us!

21:14.976 --> 21:16.676
Sam...

21:18.076 --> 21:19.676
Oh, my God!

21:19.776 --> 21:21.675
Oh, Sam, come on.

21:21.775 --> 21:23.276
Hold on, baby.

21:23.776 --> 21:25.976
Somebody's gonna come.

21:26.776 --> 21:28.775
You're going to be OK.

21:34.477 --> 21:37.676
No... Oh, God...

21:38.276 --> 21:40.076
Somebody?

21:40.276 --> 21:42.776
Somebody help me!

21:42.976 --> 21:44.776
Please, anybody!

21:44.776 --> 21:46.975
Help me, please!
Help me!

21:47.076 --> 21:49.276
OK, lady, take it
easy, all right?

21:50.876 --> 21:52.076
We'll help you, OK?

21:52.076 --> 21:56.676
Molly?

21:58.976 --> 22:00.676
<i>OK</i>

22:00.676 --> 22:02.676
<i>All right. Fine.</i>

22:02.776 --> 22:04.875
<i>What shall we do?
What shall we do?</i>

22:14.576 --> 22:16.476
What's happening?

22:16.676 --> 22:18.276
What's...

22:18.276 --> 22:20.877
<i>Is he...
Is he breathing?</i>

22:27.376 --> 22:29.276
<i>Hold on, Sam, hold on.</i>

22:29.276 --> 22:31.275
<i>Don't leave me. Hold on.</i>

22:31.275 --> 22:33.075
<i>Oh, my God.</i>

22:52.976 --> 22:54.876
Here we go.

22:55.376 --> 22:57.076
One...

23:00.176 --> 23:01.576
Sam, don't you leave me!

23:01.576 --> 23:03.475
Sam, hold on!

23:08.775 --> 23:10.775
Jesus...

23:57.074 --> 23:59.974
Miss Jensen, if you would
just step this way, please.

24:16.973 --> 24:18.374
So...

24:18.374 --> 24:20.573
What happened to you?

24:20.773 --> 24:21.773
What?

24:21.773 --> 24:23.873
You're new, huh?
I can tell.

24:24.873 --> 24:25.973
Are you talking to me?

24:25.973 --> 24:27.972
Relax, it ain't like before.

24:27.972 --> 24:30.672
It's a whole new
ball of wax.

24:31.572 --> 24:32.573
Who are you?

24:32.573 --> 24:33.573
Oh, I'm waiting for my wife.

24:33.573 --> 24:37.673
She's in the 4-C, cardiac wing.
She's fighting it.

24:46.573 --> 24:48.073
Shot, huh?

24:48.173 --> 24:50.273
That'll do it every time.

24:50.973 --> 24:52.473
Poor bastard.

24:52.973 --> 24:54.872
You may as well get used to it.

24:54.972 --> 24:57.272
You could be here
for a long while.

25:01.473 --> 25:03.772
Come here.
I'll tell you a secret.

25:03.872 --> 25:05.673
Doors ain't as
bad as you think.

25:05.873 --> 25:07.574
Zip-zap - ain't
nothing at all.

25:07.574 --> 25:09.574
You'll see.
You'll catch on.

25:14.673 --> 25:16.373
He ain't going to make it.

25:16.373 --> 25:17.973
I've seen it
a million times.

25:17.973 --> 25:20.073
He's a goner.

25:25.173 --> 25:26.472
You see?

25:26.472 --> 25:28.372
Here they come.

25:32.072 --> 25:33.772
Lucky bastard!

25:34.072 --> 25:36.272
It could have been
the other ones.

25:36.572 --> 25:38.672
You never know.

25:59.172 --> 26:00.972
Who are they?

26:05.671 --> 26:07.371
No!

26:15.571 --> 26:17.472
Help me!

26:17.572 --> 26:19.773
Oh God.

26:19.773 --> 26:21.673
Help me.

26:27.172 --> 26:29.772
I am sunk in the
abysmal swamp

26:29.772 --> 26:32.371
where there is no foothold.

26:32.371 --> 26:35.172
I have reached
the watery depths.

26:35.272 --> 26:38.272
The flood overwhelms me.

26:38.372 --> 26:40.873
I am wearied with calling.

26:41.672 --> 26:45.372
As we say farewell to
our friend, Sam Wheat

26:46.072 --> 26:48.472
we are reminded
of his kindness

26:49.272 --> 26:51.371
his generosity

26:51.871 --> 26:54.872
his buoyancy of spirit.

26:55.272 --> 26:56.973
All that we treasure

26:57.373 --> 26:59.172
our loved ones

26:59.172 --> 27:00.672
our friends

27:00.672 --> 27:02.772
our body

27:02.972 --> 27:04.773
our mind

27:05.173 --> 27:07.373
are but on loan to us.

27:07.473 --> 27:11.072
We must surrender
them all.

27:11.172 --> 27:13.772
We are all travellers
on the same road

27:13.972 --> 27:16.472
which leads to
the same end.

27:20.472 --> 27:23.572
As our loved one
enters eternal life

27:23.672 --> 27:26.171
Iet us remember that love,
too, is eternal.

